**Procedure:** Subjects were exposed individually to SCP-8561 in 1-metre increments within a 20-metre perimeter. Each exposure lasted a maximum of 10 minutes. Akiva radiation levels, viral progression rates, physiological changes and signs of theological reactivity were monitored.

**Results:** As expected, SCP-8561 exhibits miraculous capabilities in the internal alteration of biological systems belonging to Christian believers in its vicinity. The increase in akiva radiation emissions, and consequently the efficacy of SCP-8561's effects, is determined by the amount of "faith" and belief professed by the subject towards Catholic Christianity.

[[size small]]//**Notes:** It is recommended that future studies be conducted with participants whose religious beliefs are more diverse.//[[/size]]

-----
[[# LOG]]
+ LOG 8561.2.-

[[div class="blockquote" style="text-align:center;"]]
[[span class="biblical"]]//"And then the lawless one will be revealed, whom the Lord Jesus will overthrow with the breath of his mouth and destroy by the splendor of his coming."//[[/span]]
[[<]]
@@   @@— **(2 Thessalonians 2:8-12)**
[[/<]]
[[/div]]
@@ @@
**Date:** 03/11/2024

**History:** On 3 November 2024, at 06:32 CET, a body was reported to have been found at the top of Castel Sant'Angelo. The body was that of a young man aged between 19 and 21. He is currently registered as [[span class="clasificado"]][REDACTED][[/span]], an Italian national.

[[include component:image-block
|name=https://scp-sandbox-3.wdfiles.com/local--files/muk-scps/camera
|caption=Footage from CCTV between 00:40 - 00:50 AM
|width=50%
|align=right]]
On the night of 2 November, CCTV cameras on a nearby street captured the man heading towards the Castle carrying a rucksack.

At 00:49 on 3 November, the man is seen gaining access to the monument by climbing over one of the outer security fences of the site, paying little attention to his surroundings.

Finally, exactly 52 minutes after entering the Castle, the upper camera records the man leaving his rucksack and climbing onto the statue.

At 01:50 on 3 November, for no apparent reason, the camera stopped working, showing only continuous interference. Thanks to one of the Akiva sensors located in the area, readings from the site were recorded at that time until a specific hour when the sensors also ceased to function.

[[include :scp-wiki:component:image-features-source |hover-enlarge=--]
|enlarge-amount=6
|speed=250 
|float=false
|align=center
|width=100% 
|url=https://scp-sandbox-3.wikidot.com/local--files/muk-scps/achartmadebycakoh.png
|alt=alt|alt-text=Image Description Here
|add-caption=false
|caption=none
]]

The body was discovered at the scene by local authorities and undercover personnel from M.T.F. π-1, who had been temporarily deployed to the area to assist with and monitor SCP-8561. The castle remained closed to the public for 48 hours, and the case was classified as an accident resulting from an act of random vandalism.
[[collapsible show="+ Open aditional info [Clearance Lvl-4 required]" hide="- Close"]]
@@ @@
**Report**: Previous medical and psychological records of the victim. Provided by Mater Olbia Hospital (Rome). Some details have been redacted to protect the privacy of the victim and their family and friends.
@@ @@
