[[hcell]] Reason for admission [[/hcell]]
[[cell]] A 12-year-old male patient was referred by the paediatric A&E department following an acute episode of [[span style="border-bottom: 3px groove #ff0000;"]]psychomotor agitation[[/span]] at home. The family reports visual and auditory [[span style="border-bottom: 3px groove #ff0000;"]]hallucinations[[/span]] that have developed gradually over the last four months, with predominantly [[span style="border-bottom: 3px groove #ff0000;"]]religious and demonic[[/span]] content. The patient describes in detail the recurrent presence of a figure he identifies as [[span style="border: 3px groove #ff0000; border-radius: 20px;"]]"The Devil"[[/span]], who conveys instructions and interpretations of the world to him. No insight into his condition is observed. Voluntary admission at the request of his legal guardians. [[/cell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]
